          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-04-11 10:46:35.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-3152 utils: print lmm_oi correctly for old files",
        "message": "LU-3152 utils: print lmm_oi correctly for old files\n\nLustre 2.1 through 2.3 stored the MDS fid.f_seq into lmm_object_seq\nand fid.f_oid into lmm_object_id, but this was backward in Lustre\n1.8 and earlier (storing the inode == IGIF f_seq into lmm_object_id,\nand lmm_object_seq was always 0) and Lustre 2.4 and later (using this\nspace for an lu_fid).  These fields are used only in the client to\nensure inodes using DLM locks are unique, and a few error messages\nin Lustre, and here when printing out the striping for userspace.\n\nHandle this here transparently until it is fixed by LFSCK Phase 2,\nsince it will avoid potential future usage issues if it was done in\nthe kernel, since it might get confused if the version is ever used.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2dea7eb1f9169f5b504f25d271ffeb48c7500c1e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
